{
  "texts": [
    "Obtaining comprehensive information about targets is vital for guiding the subsequent drug discovery process.",
    "Prediction of protein structuresProteins in living cells continuously undergo conformational changes, altering their atomistic-level structures and binding affinities with chemicals [154].",
    "Researchers have found that certain protein conformations exhibit significantly stronger chemical binding abilities than others [171].",
    "Furthermore, a protein's shape determines its function.",
    "Erroneous protein structures may lead to toxicity and adverse reactions."
  ]
}